def transform_df(df, years):
    frames = []
    for i in range(len(years)):
        year_df = df[["country","region", str(years[i])]]
        year_df = year_df.rename(columns={str(years[i]): "score"})
        year_df['year'] = str(years[i])
        frames.append(year_df)
    result = pd.concat(frames)
    return result

def average_by_regions(df):
    years = df['year'].unique()
    regions = df['region'].unique()
    columns = ['year', 'region', 'average']

    average_by_regions = pd.DataFrame(columns = columns)
    rows = []

    for year in years:
        for source in regions:        
            mean = df.loc[((df['year'] == year) & (df['region'] == source)), 'score'].mean()
            row = [year, source, mean]
            zipped = zip(columns, row)
            row_dictionary = dict(zipped)
            rows.append(row_dictionary)

    average_by_regions = average_by_regions.append(rows)
    average_by_regions.head(100)
    return average_by_regions

In [87]:
range_ = ['#333587', '#8D3CA3','#BF3779', '#E76C00', '#F6E60B']

world_chart = alt.Chart(world).transform_lookup(
    lookup = 'country',
    from_ = alt.LookupData(data = df, 
                           key = 'country',
                           fields=['happiness score', 'country'])
).project(type = 'equalEarth'
).mark_geoshape(stroke='white', strokeWidth=0.5).encode(
    color = alt.Color('happiness score:Q', 
                      scale = alt.Scale(domain=[0, 2, 4, 6, 8], range=range_), 
                     
                      title='Happiness score',
                      legend=alt.Legend(
                            orient='none',
                            legendX=30, 
                            legendY=330,
                            direction='horizontal',
                            gradientLength = 200
                            )
                        ),
    tooltip = [
        alt.Tooltip('country:N', title='Country'),
        alt.Tooltip('happiness score:N', title='Happiness score', format='.1f')
    ],
)

world_report_2019 = (base + world_chart).properties(width = 900, height = 500, background='#EFECEA', padding=20,
                                title = alt.TitleParams(
                                text = 'Happiness score by countries',
                                subtitle = 'According to World Happiness Report, 2019',
                                **config_title
                            )
).configure_view(
    strokeWidth = 0
)
